    <script>


        function togglePanel(object,showLabel,hideLabel) {

            var hiding = (object.dom.style.display != "none");

            var animationCallback = function() {
                if (hiding) {
                    document.getElementById(showLabel).style.display = "block";
                    document.getElementById(hideLabel).style.display = "none";
                } else {
                    document.getElementById(showLabel).style.display = "none";
                    document.getElementById(hideLabel).style.display = "block";
                }
             };

            var animationSettings = {useDisplay:true, duration:0.5, easing:"easeBoth", callback:animationCallback};

            if(hiding) {
                object.slideOut('t', animationSettings);
            } else {
                object.slideIn('t', animationSettings);
            }
        }

                <tr class="articlerow">

<div class="row">
<div class="span12">
<table border="1" cellpadding="5" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1">
			<p>Trust is a cornerstone of our mission at CBS Interactive. We are committed to gaining and maintaining your trust by following a core set of <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/mPrivacy-Principles?template=template_mobilepp&amp;referer=mobilepp.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default" target="_blank">Privacy Principles</a>.<br>			<br>			<strong>Note:</strong> The CBS Interactive Privacy Policy has been updated. Please review the updated privacy policy carefully before using the CBS Interactive Services. By using any of the CBS Interactive Services, you consent to the terms of the updated privacy policy. <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/mPrivacy-Policy-FAQ?template=template_mobilepp&amp;referer=mobilepp.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default" target="_blank">Click here</a> for more information about the updates.</p>
			</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
<div class="span6">
<table border="1" cellpadding="5" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="text-align: center; background-color: #4C4C4C; color: #ffffff;">Scope of Privacy Policy</td></tr><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1">
			<p>CBS Interactive owns, operates, or provides access to, several interactive web sites and other interactive features that provide an authorized link to the <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/Privacy-Policy?template=template_mobilePrivacy&amp;referer=mobilepprivacy.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default" target="_blank">CBS Interactive Privacy Policy</a> (collectively &quot;CBS Interactive Services&quot;). This Privacy Policy, last modified on May 28, 2015, is guided by a core set of <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/mPrivacy-Principles?template=template_mobilepp&amp;referer=mobilepp.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default" target="_blank">Privacy Principles</a> and applies only to the <a href="http://www.cbsinteractive.com/brands/" target="_blank">CBS Interactive Services</a>.</p>
			

			<div style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 102, 0);"></span> <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/Privacy-Policy?template=template_mobilePrivacy&amp;referer=mobilepprivacy.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default#Scope of Privacy Policy" target="_blank">Read more</a></span></div>
			</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>

<div class="span6">
<table border="1" cellpadding="5" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="text-align: center; background-color: #4C4C4C; color: #ffffff;">Information Collected</td></tr><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1">
			<p>We collect a variety of information about you, including:</p>

			<ul><li> Information you provide directly to a CBS Interactive Services.</li><li> Information about your computer and browsing activities on the Services, including through <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/mCookies-Web-Beacons-and-Other-Similar-Technologies?template=template_mobilepp&amp;referer=mobilepp.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default" target="_blank">cookies, web beacons, and other similar technologies</a>.</li><li> Information about you from other sources where permitted by law.</li></ul>
			

			<div style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 102, 0);"></span> <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/Privacy-Policy?template=template_mobilePrivacy&amp;referer=mobileprivacy.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default#Information Collected" target="_blank">Read more</a></span></div>
			</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
<div class="span6">
<table border="1" cellpadding="5" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="text-align: center; background-color: #4C4C4C; color: #ffffff;">Use of Information</td></tr><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1">
			<p>We use the information we collect to:</p>

			<ul><li> Provide the services you request.</li><li> Tell you about offers we think you will value.</li><li> Customize the content and advertising you see.</li><li> Improve your experience on CBS Interactive Services.</li><li> As otherwise described to you at the point of collection or with your consent.</li></ul>
			

			<div style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 102, 0);"></span> <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/Privacy-Policy?template=template_mobilePrivacy&amp;referer=mobilepprivacy.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default#Use of Information" target="_blank">Read more</a></span></div>
			</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>

<div class="span6">
<table border="1" cellpadding="5" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="text-align: center; background-color: #4C4C4C; color: #ffffff;">Disclosure of Information</td></tr><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1">
			<p>We may share your information:</p>

			<ul><li> Where we have obtained your consent, including with video content and social networking services as described in our <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/mThird-Party-Social-Networking-Services?template=template_mobilepp&amp;referer=mobilepp.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default" target="_blank">Video Services Policy</a>.</li><li> With our thirdparty service providers.</li><li> With business partners who sponsor a sweepstakes, contest, or promotion; or who jointly offer a service or feature with a CBS Interactive Service.</li><li> Within the family of <a href="http://www.cbsinteractive.com/brands/" target="_blank">CBS Interactive Services</a>and <a href="http://www.cbscorporation.com/portfolio.php" target="_blank">other CBS businesses</a>.</li><li> If a CBS Interactive Servicesis sold to another company.</li><li> To protect or defend the rights of CBS Interactive or our users.</li><li> When required by law or public authorities.</li></ul>
			

			<div style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 102, 0);"></span> <a href="https://cbsi.secure.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/Privacy-Policy?template=template_mobilePrivacy&amp;referer=mobilepprivacy.com&amp;data=&amp;cfs=default#Disclosure of Information" target="_blank">Read more</a></span></div>
			</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
<div class="span6">
<table border="1" cellpadding="5" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="text-align: center; background-color: #4C4C4C; color: #ffffff;">Your Choices</td></tr><tr><td colspan="1" rowspan="1">
			<p></p>

			<ul><li> If you choose to share contact information with us, you will have the opportunity to update that information.</li><li> You can stop the delivery of commercial email messages from a CBS Interactive Servicesor service by following the instructions in any such email you receive.</li><li> You have choices about the collection and use of your information by third parties to display relevant advertisements, as described in our overview of <a href="http://cbsi.force.com/CBSi/articles/FAQ/Privacy-Policy-Highlights?template=template_mobilepp&amp;referer=mobilepp.com" target="_blank">Third Party Online Advertising</a></li><li> You also may choose to opt out of our use of data that we collect about your visits to our business partners sites to customize advertising that we serve.
